Currently the "Listing" sequence number will reset to 1, if there is a line break in the content. We wish to have the ability/function to edit the sequence number. This request is related to http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-18757.

PermittedSpacesQueryMapper contains this piece of code:

{code}
final int requiredClauseCount = Math.max(permittedSpaces.size(), 1024);
BooleanQuery.setMaxClauseCount(Math.max(requiredClauseCount, BooleanQuery.getMaxClauseCount()));
{code}

However PermittedSpacesScope only has 

{code}
BooleanQuery.setMaxClauseCount(Math.max(allSpaces.size() - visibleSpaces.size() + 100, 1024));
{code}

This may cause the following error:
{noformat}
[search.v2.lucene.LuceneSearcherImpl] search Error encounterd in lucene search: maxClauseCount is set to 1024
{noformat}

If I try to save a page like

{noformat}
|{pageflag:key=cleanup_index_home_on_index2.hkg}|blah|blah|
{noformat}

Confluence will complain about the label.

1. For some reason it only complains on subsequent edits, not the first save.
2. The error text says
{noformat}
The labels you have entered contain invalid characters (:, @, /, %, \, &, !, |, #, $, *, ;, ~, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >).
Label names and prefixes must be less than 255 characters. 
{noformat}

Dot is not in that list, but it seems it should be.

Similar to CONF-6008, but suggest the scope of this bug is just to fix the error text until CONF-6008 is done.

Don, I found one strange case where the RTE throws away data (using table-plugin-4.0.0)

h4. Fail case
* Edit the last element in table with RTE. Everything after the *style* is lost.
{noformat}
{table-plus:columnAttributes=, style="background:yellow;"}
|| A || B ||
| a | b |
{table-plus}
{noformat}

h4. Works
* Note no blank before the *style* parameter works ok
{noformat}
{table-plus:columnAttributes=,style="background:yellow;"}
|| A || B ||
| a | b |
{table-plus}
{noformat}

