When Office documents are edited through Office the notification mail will show the file name of the attachment only. It would be great to have more detailed information like what is sent when the page is edited directly (ie. changes, quick view of content).

There is no cache configuration for the ImageDetailsDto so it logs the following errors for ehcache

{noformat}
2010-02-19 15:08:44,633 WARN [main] [sf.hibernate.cache.EhCacheProvider] buildCache Could not find configuration [com.atlassian.confluence.pages.attachments.ImageDetailsDto]; using defaults.
{noformat}

Its not a huge problem because both ehcache and coherence create a cache anyway, but we should fix this up since it causes a fair amount of log spam.

We have a section with 2 columns, wiki markup:

{code}
{section:border=true}

{column:width=50%}
{recently-updated-dashboard}
{column}

{column}
{spaces}
{column}

{section}
{code}

If borders are turned off also the enclosed recently-updated-dashboard & the spaces macro do not show up the borders. Is there a trick to workaround? What we need is a section without borders, but the included macros have to show borders.
See attached screenshot!

* Enter some coloured text into the RTE
* Press Ctrl+K to insert a link over the text

The markup produced is:

{noformat}{color:#ff0000}[red text|QA:Home]{color}{noformat}

This markup does not display the selected color. Instead, the markup should be:

{noformat}[{color:#ff0000}red text{color}|QA:Home]{noformat}

