It is possible to upload attachments using the Links Browser by browsing to a file location one at a time.

It should also be possible to upload multiple attachments by dragging and dropping onto the dialog, the same way that you can on the Image Browser.

The autocomplete query sends:
{noformat}/rest/prototype/1/search.json?types=attachment&attachmentType=image%2Cword%2Cexcel%2Cpdf%2Cpowerpoint&search=name&query=test{noformat}

The {{types}} parameter is wrong and should be called {{type}}

If an auto complete returns an empty search then a java script error occurs because one of the fields is empty

{code}
// "search" REST has group object with result array
for (var i = 0, len = restObj.group.length; i < len; i++) {
    restMatrix.push(restObj.group[i].result);
}
{code}

Open the link browser, and you see the help text:

{noformat}Hint: type "[" to see a list of suggested pages and insert a link.{noformat}

I find this slightly confusing - it doesn't say where to type the character, so I try it in the Links Browser, and nothing  happens.

It would be clearer if changed to:

{noformat}Hint: type "[" in the editor to see a list of suggested pages and insert a link.{noformat}
